The paper focuses on developing an effective user-modeling approach based on mind maps and integrating a recommender system in mind-mapping and reference-management software. The paper also evaluates the impact of various variables on user-modeling effectiveness and recommends integrating recommender systems into mind-mapping applications. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) as the paper deals with user modeling and recommender systems. Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is also likely as the paper discusses recommending research papers. Machine Learning (cs.LG) is another possible sub-category as the paper evaluates the impact of various variables on user modeling effectiveness. Cybernetics (cs.CY) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) are also possible sub-categories as the paper deals with analyzing relationships between nodes and evaluating the effectiveness of recommendations displayed to users.
